g.desc: All modern browsers implement HTML5 specifications of: HTML –...
g.text: All modern browsers implement HTML5 specifications of:· HTML – about the page layouts;· CSS – about the visual styles;· JavaScript – about actions and data;· SVG – about graphics.Advance SVG depends solely on the HTML 5 specifications.

g.title: Sheet.171
g.desc: Advance SVG specifies data attributes (mark-ups) that can be ...
g.text: Advance SVG specifies data attributes (mark-ups) that can be added to the standard SVG elementsvia the HTML5 ‘data’ attributes.These mark-ups specify shape’s roles i.e.: popuplink, popup, in-page link, display boundary.

g.title: Sheet.174
g.desc: Advance SVG includes a JavaScript programm – ASVG, which runs...
g.text: Advance SVG includes a JavaScript programm – ASVG, which runs on the background and do all actions according to the mark-ups. This makes the graphics interactive and responsive.

g.text: The result of Advance SVG technique is interactive graphics that allow showing simple, at-a-glance pictures and interactively linking to contextual information via:· Popup graphics· In-page links· Hyperlinks

g.title: Sheet.363
g.desc: Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) is XML data that describes ima...
g.text: Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) is XML data that describes images as vectors instead of pixel matrix. A SVG image can be created via simple text editor or via graphic editors. One of the benefits of SVG is that it can be made interactive in the web browser.
